Date: 25/11/1933
Source: Press, The  (Acland Glossary)
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: Shandygaff.- various sorts of sheep mixed together in a yard. Wet and dry sheep together. Hence the verb use: to put wet sheep with dry ones in the woolshed in order to deceive the shearers.
